---
title: Job
layout: default
pagination:
    data: jobs
    size: 1
    alias: job
permalink: "/jobs/{{ job.title | slug }}-{{ job.id }}/"
---

<script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context" : "https://schema.org/",
    "@type" : "JobPosting",
    "title" : "{{ job.title}}",
    "description" : "{{ job.summary }}",
    "employmentType" : "{{ job.length }}, {{ job.contract }}",
    "hiringOrganization" : {
      "@type" : "Organization",
      "name" : "PA Consulting",
      "sameAs" : "https://www.paconsulting.com",
      "logo" : "https://www.paconsulting.com/Static/images/svgs/logo.svg"
    }
  }
</script>

<div class="bg-midnight colour-white pb-m">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col col-12 col-lg-10 offset-lg-1">

        <div class="hero mb-m">
          <span class="hero__intro"></span>
          <h1 class="hero__title h1">{{ job.title }}</h1>
        </div>

        <ul class="metadata-list mb-m">
          <li>
            {{ job.office }}, {{ job.city }}
          </li>
          <li>
            {{ job.length }}, {{ job.contract }}
          </li>
        </ul>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="bg-midnight colour-white sticky">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col col-12 col-lg-11 offset-lg-1">

        <ul class="tabs">
          <li aria-current="page"><a href="#role">The role</a></li>
          <li><a href="#benefits">Benefits</a></li>
          <li><a href="#process">Recruitment process</a></li>
          <li><a href="#location">Location</a></li>
          <li class="tab__cta"><a href="{{ job.applyUrl }}" class="button">Apply now</a></li>
        </ul>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container pb-l" id="role">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col col-12 col-lg-7 offset-lg-1 pt-l"> 

      <h2 class="h2">The role</h2>

      {% for f in job.description %}
        {% if f.key == "become-part-of-the-team" %}
          {{ f.content | safe }}
        {% elseif (f.key == "diversity-statement") or (f.key == "inclusion-and-diversity") %}
        {% elseif f.key == "benefits" %}
        {% else %}
          <h2 class="h2">{{ f.title }}</h2>
          {{ f.content | safe }}
        {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}

    </div>
    <div class="col col-12 col-lg-4 pt-l">
      <h2 class="h4">The team</h2>
      <p>We want you to feel at home from the start, so check out a few of the people you might work with one day soon.</p>
      <!-- TODO: insert team profile(s) -->

      <div class="team-card mb-m mt-m">
        <img src="https://picsum.photos/394/394" alt="">
        <span class="team-card__job">Head of design</span>
        <h3 class="h4">Bess Mills</h3>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Phasellus nec est sed ante bibendum malesuada. Nunc a pulvinar lectus, laoreet fringilla magna.</p>
      </div>

      {% switch job.capability %}
      {% case 'Design' %}
      <h2 class="h4">The Design team</h2>
      <p>Our strategy and design practitioners work together to create a vision for measurably improving customer experience, anchored in user needs and supporting key business objectives. This includes:</p>\
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Insight & analysis</strong> – We help our clients identify the gap between customer expectation and reality, mapping pains and opportunities through wide ranging research techniques.</li>
        <li><strong>Vision & strategy</strong> – Our proprietary methodology, Target Customer Experience mapping paints clear pictures of future, better customer experiences and shows how digital can improve service delivery on and offline.</li>
        <li><strong>Experience design</strong> – Our user-centred design processes are highly visual and collaborative, putting the user front and centre. We work on the full spectrum, from experience strategy, IA and UX, to interface design, content design, design systems, prototyping and user testing.</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="{{ '/about/teams/design' | url }}" class="button button--outline-midnight">More about design</a>
      {% case 'Engineering & DevOps' %}
      <h2 class="h4">The Engineering team</h2>
      <p>Digital engineers at PA are a community of practitioners excited by the possibilities of great technology, and motivated by delivering solutions that add value, achieve outcomes and delight. We work within multi-disciplinary teams formed of digital strategists, designers, researchers and delivery managers. </p>
      <p>From mission-critical platform engineering to global website builds, from enterprise API delivery to secure mobile applications, we have deep full stack development expertise across multiple technologies. This is backed by experts in Architecture, Quality Assurance and DevOps – as well as colleagues with deep expertise in Cloud, Artificial Intelligence, Internet of Things and Technology Innovation. </p>
      <a href="{{ '/about/teams/engineering-and-devops' | url }}" class="button button--outline-midnight">More about engineering &amp; devops</a>
      {% case 'Delivery' %}
      <h2 class="h4">The Delivery team</h2>
      <p>We help our clients map and quickly close the gap between their current and target state technology stack, governance processes, development and delivery approaches, digital skills and training as well as operational workflows and processes. Our areas of expertise include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Senior coaching and roundtable events</li>
        <li>Advising on digital team structures</li>
        <li>Training staff on new ways of working</li>
        <li>Creating digital toolkits</li>
        <li>Encouraging adoption of a more agile mindset</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="{{ '/about/teams/delivery' | url }}" class="button button--outline-midnight">More about delivery</a>
      {% case 'Transformation' %}
      <h2 class="h4">The Transformation team</h2>
      <p>We help clients understand the value digital can bring to the core of their business and transform ideas for change into action.</p>
      <p>We help our clients identify, test, size and justify future sources of value – and explain this value ambition to win support. This entails applying the culture, business models, technologies and ways of working of the internet era to help them respond to people’s raised expectations. At the core, we help translate ideas for change into action: Articulating the roadmap and mobilising the enterprise to move towards the digital ambition – for the future customer experience, business model, operating framework, platforms, products, propositions, and culture.</p>
      <a href="{{ '/about/teams/transformation' | url }}" class="button button--outline-midnight">More about transformation</a>
      {% endswitch %}
      
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{% include "benefits.njk" %}

<div class="container pt-l pb-l" id="process">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col col-11 offset-1">

      <h2 class="h3 mb-0">Recruitment process</h2>

    </div>
    <div class="col col-10 col-lg-6 offset-2 mt-l">

      <!-- TODO: swap this out per capability -->
      <div class="steps">
        <ol>
          <li>
            <span class="h4">Online application</span>
            <p>First up, get started by applying online. Your dream job could be waiting for you!</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="h4">First-round interview</span>
            <p>We want to understand why you’ve applied and what interests you. We’ll ask you about a few bits from your CV and hope to hear how your experiences have shaped your skills. These interviews typically last around 30 minutes.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="h4">Second round interview</span>
            <p>In the Design team we'll ask you to share a portfolio of your work and talk us through areas of interest.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="h4">Final round interview</span>
            <p>Congrats, you’ve made it to the final stage! You’ll be interviewed by a Partner or Senior Manager from your team – either in person or over the phone – for up to one hour. This is also your chance to ask any burning questions, so make sure you have these ready.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>


    </div>

    <!-- TODO: swap this out per capability -->
    <div class="col col-12 col-lg-4 job--process">
      <div class="decoration decoration--circle decoration--circle__xlg"></div>
      <h3 class="h4">Preparation tips</h3>
      <p>Remember, we’ll already have looked at your portfolio, so this is your chance to tell us a bit more about the context and challenges you faced, and any successes or failures. Don’t just repeat what we’ve already read. Consider also sharing some new examples, so we can really get a feel for the breadth and depth of your work. </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

